{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cecf3374-4d7b-422d-8518-93b3a704885b","content":"In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are gone. The equivalent is to use **`Window` lifecycle events**. Override `CreateWindow` in your `Application` class and return a custom `Window`:\n\n```csharp\npublic class App : Application\n{\n    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    {\n        var window = new Window(new MainPage());\n\n        window.Created += (s, e) => { /* OnStart */ };\n        window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep */ };\n        window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* OnResume */ };\n\n        return window;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAlternatively, subclass `Window` and override `OnCreated()`, `OnStopped()`, and `OnResumed()` for a cleaner separation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ee1251a4-1719-4bb4-a769-27b99354597a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` class.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. Instead of those virtual methods on `Application`, you use the `Window` lifecycle events or the cross-platform lifecycle events via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`, or you can override lifecycle methods on the `Window` class.\n\n\nActually, I need to clarify — .NET MAUI removed those virtual methods from the `Application` class entirely. Instead, you work with `Window` lifecycle events like `Created` (replacing `OnStart`), `Resumed` (replacing `OnResume`), and `Stopped` (replacing `OnSleep`).\n\nIf you want more control, you can subclass `Window` and override those methods directly, then wire it up by overriding `CreateWindow()` in your application class.","outputTokens":595,"requestId":"E858:D4E0A:2656C81:2A64FEB:69F93F5D"},"id":"84296142-72ec-4d46-b9fc-c42d2ba55ffb","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:52:56.648Z","parentId":"8276ad8a-f34e-414f-a316-e75e7aaefc23"}
